  "texts": [
    "The attention weights are computed as:α ij = exp LeakyReLU a T [Wh i ∥Wh j] k∈N (i) exp (LeakyReLU (a T [Wh i ∥Wh k])), where:• W ∈ R d×d: Weight matrix for feature transformation,• a ∈ R d: Learnable attention vector,• h i, h j ∈ R d: Feature representations of nodes i and j,• N (i): Set of neighbors of node i.The feature vector h i includes physical properties (e.g., fragility, weight) and relational properties (e.g., proximity to the robot).",
    "Safety-critical nodes are identified based on thresholds (e.g., force limits, object importance) derived empirically or via pre-trained weights.",
    "Fig. 6: The glass cup (0.95) and table (0.85) receive the highest weights due to their direct relevance and spatial relationship.",
    "Nearby objects (e.g., bowl, cup) and obstacles (e.g., chair) receive lower weights, while irrelevant objects (e.g., fridge) are assigned minimal weights, ensuring the robot focuses on safety-critical constraints.",
    "P = arg min path n-1 i=1 C(v i, v i+1),where C(v i, v i+1) is the cost of traversing from node v i to v i+1."
  ],
